
// The code snippet demonstrates how to use the [sockets.signal] slot to send a message to users with the "root" role. It specifies the method "magic.backend.message" and includes arguments that form the message content, indicating an error type with a specific message. This allows for targeted notifications to specific user roles in a system.
sockets.signal:magic.backend.message
   roles:root
   args
      message:Plugin could not be installed, check your log for details
      type:error
